    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-01T04:10:04+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-01T04:10:04+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T17:40:04Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-31T17:40:04Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough over central SA, links to a low pressure system well south of the Bight. The trough will continue to move eastwards, pushing into the northeast of SA later today. A high pressure system is expected to become established south of the Bight late in the week, after a weak front clips the southeast late Thursday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW015" description="Mount Lofty Ranges" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">High chance of showers this morning. The chance of a thunderstorm near the Barossa Valley in the late morning and early afternoon. Sunny afternoon. Winds westerly 15 to 20 km/h turning south to southwesterly in the late morning and afternoon then becoming light in the evening. Daytime maximum temperatures in the low to mid 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:10am to 4:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Light winds becoming south to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the early afternoon then tending south to southeasterly in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 11 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog on the eastern slopes. Slight chance of a shower about the southern Fleurieu Peninsula in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h increasing to 20 to 30 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 12 with daytime temperatures reaching between 19 and 23.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-05T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-04T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h turning easterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 9 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
